Savour a taste of Trinidad and feel the Indian influence. Epic chicken dishes served from bright-yellow containers. Roll up for a classic dosa and chai at either of two locations, on Grand Canal Street in Dublin 2 and on Prussia Street in Dublin 7. Mexican tacos served from a Los Angeles-style truck. Virtuous smoothie bowls and horsebox coffee served beachside. Wood-fired pizza outside Clifden from a unique hand-built truck. Stunning seafood, including barbecued lobster. New Zealand–influenced dishes with Sligo ingredients served riverside. Be spoiled for choice in Cork’s old Ford factory—Marina Market has 21 food vendors according to the most recent count. A roving food truck serving hyperlocal food across the country. Recent stops have included Ennistymon, in Co Clare, and Kill, in Co Kildare.